text: Suresh Angadi (1 June 1955 â€“ 23 September 2020) was an Indian politician. He was a member of parliament from 2004 until his death. He was Minister of State for Railways from 2019 until his death in 2020. He was a leader of Bharatiya Janata Party from Karnataka. He was born in Karnataka, India. Angadi died on 23 September 2020 at a hospital in New Delhi from COVID-19 at the age of 65. ==References== Category:1955 births Category:2020 deaths Category:Deaths from the COVID-19 pandemic in New Delhi Category:Politicians from Karnataka
